# Performance (Spark)

## Before claiming "slow"
Profile with Instruments (Time Profiler, SwiftUI, Allocations) or MetricKit — no drive-by micro-optimizations.

## Lists & images
- `LazyVStack` / `LazyHStack` for lists >20 items; cursor pagination at ~80% scroll
- `AsyncImage` with phase UI, or Nuke via SPM if advanced caching needed
- Downsample images to display size; coalesce network requests

## SwiftUI lifecycle
- `.task(id:)` for loads; respect `CancellationError`
- Prefetch next page in background `Task` with low priority when appropriate
- No retain cycles — `[weak self]` only in escaping closures that capture self

## Background & battery
- `BackgroundTasks` for deferrable work; respect Low Power / Low Data Mode
- Avoid redundant Firestore/listener churn; cache with documented invalidation

## Targets (document exceptions in PR)
- Cold launch P95 ≤ 1.5s to interactive (mid-tier device)
- Feed scroll 60fps; idle memory baseline documented per screen
